export JAVA_HOME="/Applications/Android Studio.app/Contents/jre/jdk/Contents/Home"
export ANDROID_HOME="/Users/admin/Library/Android/sdk"



Things to be done after node_modules installed:
1. Create an folder named `assets` in the android/app/src/main
2. modify the metro-config in the node_modules
3. access to the src/defaults/blacklist.js
4. Replace : 

var sharedBlacklist = [
  /node_modules[/\\]react[/\\]dist[/\\].*/,
  /website\/node_modules\/.*/,
  /heapCapture\/bundle\.js/,
  /.*\/__tests__\/.*/
];

with : 

var sharedBlacklist = [
  /node_modules[\/\\]react[\/\\]dist[\/\\].*/,
  /website\/node_modules\/.*/,
  /heapCapture\/bundle\.js/,
  /.*\/__tests__\/.*/
];

5. go to back to the project root and run the following command:
react-native bundle --platform android --dev false --entry-file index.js --bundle-output android/app/src/main/assets/index.android.bundle --assets-dest android/app/src/main/res


6. *****IMPORTANT*****
- if you have index.android.bundle in the folder, please remove it first then only proceed to the 5th step
- if the the 5th step shows error, please remove package-lock.jason and remove the node_moudules, reinstall it and start from step 1 again.
